  "prompt": "What is the sense of smell?",
  "response": "The sense of smell, also known as olfaction, is one of the five traditional senses. It is the ability of the body to detect and identify different scents or odors through the detection of chemicals in the air. This sense is facilitated by olfactory receptor cells located in the nasal cavity, which are specialized sensory neurons that transmit signals to the brain, specifically the olfactory bulb, where the sensation of smell is processed and perceived. The sense of smell plays an important role in our daily lives, influencing our taste, food preferences, emotional memories, and even our safety by alerting us to potential dangers such as fire or spoiled food.",
